{"info": {"author": "Mike Steder", "author_email": "steder@gmail.com", "bugtrack_url": null, "classifiers": ["Development Status :: 3 - Alpha", "Intended Audience :: Developers", "License :: OSI Approved :: MIT License", "Programming Language :: Python"], "description": "=================================\nTwistr\n=================================\n\n`Twistr` is a simple wrapper around the Twisted_ projects `twistd` commandline\ntool that will restart the server whenever python files change.\n\n---------------------------------\nUsage\n---------------------------------\n\nFrom your root project directory (where your `twisted/plugins` folder lives)\nlaunch your service with::\n\n  twistr -n <service>\n\nOr even::\n\n  twistr <service>\n\nNow change a `*.py` file in your current directory and watch your server\nmagically restart.\n\n---------------------------------\nTODO\n---------------------------------\n\n * configurable directory to watch for changes\n * configurable file extensions to watch for changes\n * use filesystem events API(s) to watch for changes\n\n.. _Twisted: http://www.twistedmatrix.com/\n\n\n", "description_content_type": "", "docs_url": null, "download_url": "", "downloads": {"last_day": -1, "last_month": -1, "last_week": -1}, "home_page": "http://github.com/steder/twistr", "keywords": "", "license": "MIT", "maintainer": "", "maintainer_email": "", "name": "Twistr", "package_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Twistr/", "platform": "", "project_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Twistr/", "project_urls": {"Homepage": "http://github.com/steder/twistr"}, "release_url": "https://pypi.org/project/Twistr/2.0.0/", "requires_dist": ["twisted"], "requires_python": "", "summary": "Twistd wrapper that restarts twisted on code changes", "version": "2.0.0", "yanked": false, "html_description": "<div class=\"project-description\">\n            <p><cite>Twistr</cite> is a simple wrapper around the <a href=\"http://www.twistedmatrix.com/\" rel=\"nofollow\">Twisted</a> projects <cite>twistd</cite> commandline\ntool that will restart the server whenever python files change.</p>\n<div id=\"usage\">\n<h2>Usage</h2>\n<p>From your root project directory (where your <cite>twisted/plugins</cite> folder lives)\nlaunch your service with:</p>\n<pre>twistr -n &lt;service&gt;\n</pre>\n<p>Or even:</p>\n<pre>twistr &lt;service&gt;\n</pre>\n<p>Now change a <cite>*.py</cite> file in your current directory and watch your server\nmagically restart.</p>\n</div>\n<div id=\"todo\">\n<h2>TODO</h2>\n<blockquote>\n<ul>\n<li>configurable directory to watch for changes</li>\n<li>configurable file extensions to watch for changes</li>\n<li>use filesystem events API(s) to watch for changes</li>\n</ul>\n</blockquote>\n</div>\n\n          </div>"}, "last_serial": 5402310, "releases": {"1.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "be47c025614a4904674c95e317ec4e0e", "sha256": "8a3b03485aaf2b63f433e34ff50e9b7a2c922dc3941080ee0a5315d4899345f1"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "Twistr-1.0.0.tar.gz", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "be47c025614a4904674c95e317ec4e0e", "packagetype": "sdist", "python_version": "source", "requires_python": null, "size": 3182, "upload_time": "2012-10-02T16:29:17", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2012-10-02T16:29:17.134540Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/01/a6/64a244cdf69c9f2a29eefbf0f6fa0ba168a76b075a358fa13dc06b1c3ef4/Twistr-1.0.0.tar.gz", "yanked": false}], "2.0.0": [{"comment_text": "", "digests": {"md5": "fba0c1947caf9818c45bdf3f79bc8bd9", "sha256": "bf21364b4bcd07388eb8d16ae8a1ec75d86e7689a02ca87d70c55fe915b37b94"}, "downloads": -1, "filename": "Twistr-2.0.0-py3-none-any.whl", "has_sig": false, "md5_digest": "fba0c1947caf9818c45bdf3f79bc8bd9", "packagetype": "bdist_wheel", "python_version": "py3", "requires_python": null, "size": 3578, "upload_time": "2019-06-14T21:53:21", "upload_time_iso_8601": "2019-06-14T21:53:21.578012Z", "url": "https://files.pythonhosted.org/packages/e6/27/75cc8ec7a5f0a0fcd034e1311042489a4fabe00